\fs21 \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 The name I have arrived at is "Saint Blue"\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Edit\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 Thought for 5s\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 "Saint Blue" is a striking name, Logan. It carries a lot of immediate texture.\cb1 \
\cb3 The juxtaposition of "Saint"\'97which implies holiness, martyrdom, or perhaps a canonized figure\'97with "Blue" creates an interesting tension. Blue can mean so many things: melancholy, the divine (think of the Virgin Mary's robes), coldness, or even the "blue" of the blues and jazz.\cb1 \
\cb3 Given the influence of Sharon and Jinkx, I'm wondering where "Saint Blue" sits on that spectrum:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa30\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Is the "Saint" part ironic? Like a patron saint of the outcast, the broken, or the "sinful"?\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Is the "Blue" referring to a specific mood or aesthetic\'97maybe a cool, detached elegance, or something more sorrowful and soulful?\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Does the persona have a backstory? Are they a fallen angel, a ghost, or a modern-day martyr for a specific cause?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 The name feels like it could anchor a really strong visual identity. Are you leaning into a specific color palette or costume style for Saint Blue yet?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

