\fs21 \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 Deer Antlers \'97 a female woman with a young buck's ornaments on her crown\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Edit\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 Thought for 9s\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 That imagery is incredibly potent, Logan. A "female woman" (a beautiful, perhaps hyper-feminine figure) crowned with the antlers of a young buck creates a striking visual dissonance. It immediately suggests a few compelling themes:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa30\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 The Hunted vs. The Hunter:
\f0\b0 \'a0Antlers are weapons and symbols of dominance, but on a feminine frame, they can also look like a crown of vulnerability\'97the prey wearing the trophy of the predator.\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Nature and the Sacred:
\f0\b0 \'a0The combination of the "Saint" title with animalistic horns evokes ancient pagan deities or forest spirits (like Cernunnos, but feminized). It feels mythic, almost like a fable brought to life.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Growth and Shedding:
\f0\b0 \'a0A "young buck" implies something in transition, growing into its power. Antlers are shed and regrown annually, which could mirror the cyclical nature of drag itself\'97putting on a mask, performing, and then taking it off to start again.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 Visually, I imagine this could be stunning. Are you thinking of the antlers as part of a headdress made of real materials (velvet, bone, metal), or something more stylized and abstract? And does Saint Blue have a specific "vibe" or personality that matches this look? Is she serene and distant, or perhaps wild and untamed beneath the surface?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

