\cb3 You found the "job"\'97the stable, respectable career at Idaho Public Television, the award-winning journalist, the public figure in Boise. You secured the survival. But in doing so, you traded the "lake and the trees" of your youth for the "high sagebrush desert." You traded the wild, damp freedom of the rainforest for the dry, exposed heat of a political climate that feels increasingly hostile to the very parts of you that make you whole.\cb1 \
