\f2\b Masking
\f0\b0 \'a0is a well-documented phenomenon, particularly in the autistic community, where individuals consciously or unconsciously suppress their natural behaviors, stims, and communication styles to fit neurotypical expectations and avoid social punishment.\cb1 \
\cb3 If you are considering that you might be autistic (or at least that masking is a primary driver of your exhaustion), it reframes the "Professional" persona not just as a career shield, but as a\'a0
