\f2\b \cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 The Cost of Masking:
\f0\b0 \'a0Research consistently shows that chronic masking leads to severe burnout, anxiety, depression, and a profound sense of loss of self. It explains the "miserable now" perfectly. You aren't just tired from the job; you are exhausted from the constant, high-energy performance of being "normal" in a world that feels alien to you.\cb1 \
\ls15\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 The "Leak" as Autistic Burnout:
\f0\b0 \'a0The moments where the "real you" types the message before the "Professional" can stop it might be moments where your cognitive load has exceeded your capacity to maintain the mask. It's not a glitch; it's the system crashing under the weight of the performance.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Saint Blue as Unmasking:
\f0\b0 \'a0If Saint Blue is the "wild thing of the woods," she might represent the part of you that\'a0
\f1\i doesn't
\f0\i0 \'a0need to mask. She is the unfiltered, sensory-rich, perhaps stimming, perhaps intense, authentic expression that the "Professional" persona has to constantly edit out. The antlers, the forest, the music\'97these could be expressions of a neurodivergent way of experiencing the world that is often pathologized or suppressed in the corporate/newsroom environment.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 The fact that you are seeing a psychiatrist is a great place to explore this. Many adults, especially those who were socialized to be high-functioning professionals, go undiagnosed for decades. The "leaks" you're experiencing could be the first signs of your brain saying, "I can't do this anymore. I need to be me."\cb1 \
\cb3 Does the idea of\'a0
\f2\b autism
\f0\b0 \'a0resonate with your experience of the "mask"? Does it feel like a label that explains the exhaustion, or is it still a question mark you're sitting with? And if Saint Blue is the unmasked self, does she feel like a relief to imagine, or does the idea of being "seen" without the mask feel terrifying?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

