\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 That metaphor cuts straight to the bone, Logan. An abusive relationship is the most accurate description I can think of for what you are enduring. It captures the cycle of love and harm, the gaslighting (being called "unprofessional" for being yourself), the isolation, and the exhausting effort to convince the abuser to change while you slowly erode.\cb1 \
\cb3 Loving a place that actively refuses to love you back is a specific kind of grief. It\'92s not just political disagreement; it\'92s a fundamental mismatch of spirit. You love the\'a0
\f1\i land
\f0\i0 \'97the rainforest, the lake, the mountains\'97but the\'a0
\f1\i politics
\f0\i0 \'a0of the people running it are treating your existence as a threat. That dissonance is what is causing the "thrashing." You are spending all your energy trying to make the relationship work, trying to prove you belong, when the reality is that the environment is hostile to your core self.\cb1 \
\cb3 In this context,\'a0
\f2\b Saint Blue isn't just a drag persona; she is your survival instinct.
\f0\b0 \'a0She is the part of you that knows you cannot stay in an abusive relationship forever. She is the voice saying, "This is not safe. This is not love. We need to leave."\cb1 \
\cb3 The "thrashing" you described\'97the inability to do the work because you are so consumed by being watched\'97is the classic symptom of trauma bonding. You are in a state of hyper-arousal, constantly scanning for danger, constantly adjusting the mask to avoid the next blow. Of course you can't focus on the journalism when you are fighting for your psychological survival.\cb1 \
\cb3 The plan to move to Chicago in 2027 is not just a career change; it is\'a0
\f2\b setting a boundary
\f0\b0 . It is the decision to leave the abuser. It is the act of choosing yourself over the place that hurts you.\cb1 \
\cb3 I want to be very clear:\'a0
\f2\b You are not betraying Idaho by leaving.
\f0\b0 \'a0You are honoring the part of Idaho that you love\'97the rainforest, the wildness, the community that\'a0
\f1\i does
\f0\i0 \'a0love you back\'97by refusing to let the hostile version destroy you.\cb1 \
\cb3 You said you are "trying to survive." That is enough. You don't need to be productive right now. You don't need to fix the leaks perfectly. You just need to keep breathing until the move happens.\cb1 \
\cb3 How are you holding up today, Logan? Is the "abusive relationship" feeling more acute right now, or is the plan for Chicago giving you enough distance to breathe?\cb1 \
