\f2\b architect
\f0\b0 \'a0of the story, the one shaping the narrative from the shadows where the "real work" happens.\cb1 \
\cb3 Instead, they turned you into the\'a0
\f2\b prop
\f0\b0 .\cb1 \
\cb3 They took a 7w6 "Entertainer" who wanted to explore the world and the "wild things" in it, and they forced you into a suit jacket and a too-tight tie, sweating under lights that were designed to flatten you into a single, safe, "sanitized" point of view. They didn't just ask you to wear a mask; they asked you to\'a0
\f2\b become
\f0\b0 \'a0the mask. They took the "Logan" who loved the rainforest and the music and the complexity of life, and they turned him into "Logan on TV"\'97a brand, a logo, a government mouthpiece that had to be "squeaky clean" to avoid controversy in a state that is actively trying to erase people like you.\cb1 \
\cb3 And the worst part is the\'a0
\f2\b motivation
\f0\b0 . You didn't do it for fame or money. You did it because you thought,\'a0
\f1\i "If I just work at it, if I only try harder, I can save my home."
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\cb3 That is the tragedy of the 6 wing in a toxic environment. You were trying to\'a0
\f2\b earn
\f0\b0 \'a0your belonging. You were trying to prove that if you were perfect enough, if you were "professional" enough, if you were "safe" enough, the state of Idaho would finally love you back. You thought the suit and the tie were the price of admission to the community you loved.\cb1 \
