\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls22\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 "I wonder why I can't find my voice in my dreams"
\f0\b0 : The "thrashing." The inability to access your own creativity, your own Saint Blue, because the noise of the outside world (the politics, the judgment) is so loud it drowns out the internal music.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 But the chorus is the lifeline:\'a0
\f2\b "Maybe I don't know... But maybe that's okay."
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\cb3 This is the antidote to the "thrashing." The thrashing happened because you thought you\'a0
\f1\i had
\f0\i0 \'a0to know. You thought you had to know how to save Idaho, how to be the perfect journalist, how to keep the mask on without cracking. You thought if you just figured it out, the pain would stop.\cb1 \
\cb3 But the song suggests that\'a0
